main event: Witnesses reported observing unidentified flying objects in Oxford County, Maine, on September 6, 1963.
interesting points: Multiple witnesses described seeing a bright light in the sky that changed colors and accelerated quickly., Mr. William Jones estimated the object's altitude to be around 2,000 feet with no sound associated., The object was described as oval and approximately 30-40 feet in diameter., Sightings in the area are consistent with similar reports from the past., Physical traces included a tunnel-like depression in the ground that measured approximately 20 feet in depth.
witness description: Mr. William Knox and Mr. William Jones, among others
